\begin_layout Abstract
Here you see the most important template updates for October, 2015.
 We have newly enhanced 
\family typewriter

\backslash
committee
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter

\backslash
role
\family default
 environments.
 Now, we allow users to specify up to 7 committee members and each one can
 have a different role.
 Why provide all of this luxury? There were unexpected requests from students.
 The original KU Thesis template had only 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Chair
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for the first member.
 Users asked for a secondary title 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Co-Chair
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for member 2.
 Then they wanted to change the title of the first member to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Lead Chair
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Then they wanted to add a the third Co-Chair, and so forth.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
Now we accommodate those requests by leaving blank spots for up to seven
 committee members and seven roles.
 It is vital for you to leave the blank place holders {} if you don't want
 to list additional members or roles.
 This example document shows some funny titles, we do that only to prove
 it is possible.
 Generally, there is only a Chair, possibly a Co-Chair.
 This example has more roles in this example for fun.
 Or to make fun of a professor.
 You can change them to {}, of course, if you don't want a named role.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The other thing to change is the date section.
 Lower in the preamble, you should see a place to insert some dates.
 Originally, we told students 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

just write those dates in by hand, like we did back in the olden days.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 But they kept saying they wanted them type set, so here they are.
 If a date is currently unknown, just leave a blank inside the brackets
\end_layout

