\begin_layout Abstract
Why does \SpecialChar LyX
 work? When the user asks \SpecialChar LyX
 to preview the PDF output, a two step
 process happens behind the scenes.
 A file named 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\family typewriter
thesis-ku.tex
\family default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is created in a temporary directory, and then a program like 
\family typewriter
\series bold
pdflatex
\family default
\series default
 is asked to turn that into a PDF document.
 \SpecialChar LyX
 will then send the PDF output to a PDF viewer, such as Yapp, Evince or
 Acrobat.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
How to silence the LyX warnings.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
\noindent

\series bold
1.
 Copy the LyX layout file 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\family typewriter
kuthesis.layout
\family default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 into the layout folder of the user configuration.
\series default

\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
The only problem is finding the correct user configuration folder.
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
On
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Linux, copy 
\family typewriter
kuthesis.layout
\family default
 into the user HOME folder, under 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\family typewriter
.lyx/layouts
\family default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
On
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Windows, there is a hidden AppData directory inside the user's home folder.
 How to find it? Run \SpecialChar LyX
.
 A window should appear with a row of pull down menus at the top.
 Choose Tools/Preferences.
 Change something trivial, then close the menu.
 That will force \SpecialChar LyX
 to create a user folder.
 Then search inside your user directory for a key word such as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

lyxrc.defaults
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Probably, searching for 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

*lyx*
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 will be sufficient.
 In MS Windows 7, I found 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

C:
\backslash
Users
\backslash
pauljohn
\backslash
AppData
\backslash
Roaming
\backslash
lyx212
\backslash
layouts
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Caution: The AppData folder is hidden/concealed and, in order to find it
 in Windows Explorer, it is necessary to change the folder options to NOT
 hide protected files and folders.
 Windows 10 is very similar.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
On
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Macintosh
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

OS
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

X, we recently followed same 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

change a setting, then search
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 procedure.
 The answer was 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

/Users/pauljohn/Library/Application Support/\SpecialChar LyX
-2.1/layouts
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Documentation for OS X El Capitan indicates that Apple has followed the
 Microsoft policy of hiding this folder, so the person who uses the Finder
 will have to change some preferences to show the directory.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Abstract

\series bold
2.
 Copy the LaTeX class file 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\family typewriter
kuthesis.cls
\family default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 into the LaTeX distribution and then do the appropriate reconfiguration.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
Again, if you have done this before, it is no big deal.
 If you have not done it before, it seems daunting.
 We described it in an earlier, under the heading 
\series bold
How to Configure your LaTeX Distribution with kuthesis.cls
\series default
.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
\noindent

\series bold
3.
 Let LyX find your changes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
\noindent
In LyX, find the pull down menu item Tools -> Reconfigure.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
After that, LyX should work and not warn you about files it thinks it does
 not have.
 Once again, it is not necessary to do these reconfigurations, but LyX will
 not warn about missing pieces anymore.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
We notice that LyX is not, by default, configured to do spell-checking as
 you type.
 This is a vestigial setting, a reflection of the days long ago when people
 knew how to spell.
 To turn on the spell checker, use the pull down menu 
\family typewriter
Tools
\family default
 -> 
\family typewriter
Preferences
\family default
 -> 
\family typewriter
Language Settings
\family default
 -> 
\family typewriter
Spellchecker
\family default
.
 One must choose a program to serve as the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Spellchecker engine
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and then click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Spellcheck Continously
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 The Spellchecker engine I use in Ubuntu Linux is called Enchant.
 I expect you will find one in your operating system, or can find one.
 If not, we may have to ask Mr.
 Google for help.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract

\series bold
Other friendly advice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract

\emph on
Compile Early, Compile Often
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The truly bad part of using \SpecialChar LaTeX
 is that the errors and warnings are, generally,
 not understandable.
 They are not understandable to me and I've been using \SpecialChar LaTeX
 for about 20 years.
 I mean, well, they are simply too abstract.
 Too complicated.
 If you insert an illegal character, such as an 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

_
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 in a \SpecialChar LaTeX
 box, the document will fail with this unhelpful message
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
\begin_inset listings
lstparams "breaklines=true,tabsize=2"
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Missing $ inserted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Missing $ inserted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Missing } inserted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Extra }, or forgotten 
\backslash
endgroup.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

I've inserted a begin-math/end-math symbol since I think you left one out.
 Proceed, with fingers crossed.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
\noindent
At best, the message will point to the line you inserted to cause the problem,
 but often the \SpecialChar LaTeX
 system cannot guess where your mistake is, it can only say
 something is wrong.
 The best way to defend yourself: 
\series bold
\shape italic
Compile Early, Compile Often
\shape default
.
 
\series default
Don't make a lot of changes without trying to compile.
 It is easy to insert a feature that breaks the document.
 Compile often so you know when things have gone wrong.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract

\emph on
Use a Version Management System!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
If this is an important project, please consider installing Git or some
 other version management program.
 It is difficult to avoid clutter if you have to rename your file every
 day.
 I see user directories full of files named, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

my_diss.lyx
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

my_diss.2.lyx
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

my_diss_final.lyx
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

my_diss_rejected.lyx
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and so forth.
 It is very difficult to keep old and new versions straight unless you use
 a version manager.
 A version manager will handle that for you.
 You will just have one file 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

my_diss.lyx
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and you will have the ability to compare old and new snapshots.
 The CRMDA has a more-or-less comprehensive, yet easy to follow guide for
 Git, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Git it Together
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
I urge you to keep your \SpecialChar LaTeX
 document in Git so you can make frequent commits
 and it will be easy to step back in time.
 This is one reason why you should work on separate chapters, so if you
 break something, then you are more likely to find your mistakes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract

\emph on
KU requires that fonts be compiled with the final result
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The pdflatex compiler will insert fonts when it compiles the document.
 However, there is a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

gotcha
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 If you create PDF documents separately, and you forget to embed the fonts
 with them, then the KU Graduate Dean's office is likely to reject your
 thesis.
 When a PDF is included within this document, pdflatex does not check to
 see if fonts are embedded in those PDFs.
 It assumes they are as you want them; fonts for those included files are
 not automatically inserted by pdflatex.
 When a graph, for example, is created in R and exported to PDF, it will
 not include the font encodings by default.
 It is possible to add those encodings.
 Little details like this come up from time to time and we make note of
 them in 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

https://crmda.ku.edu/latex-help
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract

\emph on
If you need help, ask, but please understand 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
I don't have as much time as I would like to help users.
 I want you to use \SpecialChar LaTeX
.
 I think doing anything else is finger painting.
 I've watched 20 MA and PhD theses written with this template and I know
 a bright student will succeed and be happy with the result.
 If you have a laptop computer and you want to show me some errors, I can
 give you 5 or 10 minutes.
 But not much more...
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
CRMDA offers some workshops and I teach graduate courses in which we show
 how to use \SpecialChar LaTeX
.
 If you find something wrong with kuthesis.cls, I will be glad to try to
 fix it.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
I don't have time/ability to answer a million email questions about \SpecialChar LaTeX
 or
 \SpecialChar LyX
.
 If you are stuck on a tough problem, I may be able to help, but if I have
 to exert myself, you should know I expect you to give me a t-shirt and/or
 add me to the acknowledgements in your dissertation.
\end_layout

